            <ul id="rent" class="cd-faq-group">
                <li class="cd-faq-title"><h2>Renting a car</h2></li>
                {% embed '@Guide/component/faq-item.html.twig' %}
                    {% block faq_title %}Rental terms{% endblock %}

                    {% block faq_content %}


                        Most of the known international car rental services operate in Russia. They usually have their offices at the airports.
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        <a href="http://www.hertz.ru/rentacar/reservation/">Hertz</a><br>
                        <a href="http://www.avisrussia.ru/">Avis</a><br>
                        <a href="http://www.rentalcars.com/ru/brand/alamo/">Alamo</a><br>
                        <a href="http://www.dollarrent.ru ">Dollar</a><br>
                        <br>
                        <p>
                            Ordinarily, you have to be 21 or older to rent an A or B class car, and 23 or older to rent
                            a C class car or
                            higher. You have to show your ID and your driver’s license to rent a car, and your license
                            has to be at
                            least 12 months old. The major rentals will ask for one or two valid bank cards to secure a
                            deposit.&nbsp;
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The deposit amount will vary between the different rental companies.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The majority of car rental companies require a deposit to cover the possible mutilation of
                            the parts that
                            are not covered by insurance, such as tires, mirrors, window glass, and also to cover the
                            fuel and franchise
                            costs. The deposit will be refunded when the client returns the car intact with a full
                            gasoline tank. It may
                            take anything between two days and a month for the deposit to be refunded to your card.
                        </p>
                    {% endblock %}
                {% endembed %}

                {% embed '@Guide/component/faq-item.html.twig' %}
                    {% block faq_title %}Insurance{% endblock %}

                    {% block faq_content %}


                        <p>
                            There are two types of auto insurance in Russia: statutory (OSAGO) and optional (CASCO).
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The statutory auto insurance law (OSAGO) stipulates the top limit of 400,000 roubles for the
                            sum insured. In
                            the event of an accident resulting in a fatality, the insurer will compensate the survivors
                            up to a maximum
                            of 500,000 roubles. &nbsp;
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The terms of optional insurance (CASCO), including the sum insured, are subject to the
                            contract between the
                            insurer and the party insured. A CASCO policy often comes with a franchise, which is the
                            stipulation that
                            the insurer will not be liable to indemnify below a certain amount of damage, in which case
                            the sum below
                            the bottom limit will be left for the account of the party insured.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <a href="http://welcome2018.com/guide/77989/">Accident in a rental car</a>
                        </p>

                    {% endblock %}
                {% endembed %}
            </ul> <!-- cd-faq-group -->

            <ul id="ride" class="cd-faq-group">
                <li class="cd-faq-title"><h2>Ride sharing</h2></li>
                {% embed '@Guide/component/faq-item.html.twig' %}
                    {% block faq_title %}Available services{% endblock %}

                    {% block faq_content %}

                        Ride sharing is a budget way to move between cities. Ride sharing is when someone who is driving to
                        another town takes passengers for a modest fee. The online ride sharing services will require
                        registration to put you in touch with a driver going in your direction. The caveat here is that your
                        safety is your own responsibility: the service provider will accept no responsibility for anything
                        that happens on the trip. <br>
                        <br>
                        <a href="http://www.blablacar.ru ">BlaBlaCar</a><br>
                        <a href="http://beepcar.ru/">Beepcar</a><br>
                        <a href="http://www.dovezu.ru/">Dovezu</a><br>
                    {% endblock %}
                {% endembed %}
            </ul> <!-- cd-faq-group -->

            <ul id="car" class="cd-faq-group">
                <li class="cd-faq-title"><h2>Car Sharing</h2></li>
                {% embed '@Guide/component/faq-item.html.twig' %}
                    {% block faq_title %}App list{% endblock %}

                    {% block faq_content %}

                        <p>
                            Car sharing services are available in the 2018 World Cup host cities. Car sharing is
                            short-term
                            car rental where you pay by the minute.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The rate is basically the same with all car sharing providers: about 8 roubles per minute.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            To be able to use this service, you have to download a mobile app, register in the system,
                            sign
                            a service contract (at their offices or via courier), and link your bank card to your
                            account in
                            the system. Now you are ready to use a car sharing service.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            There are several car sharing providers in Moscow. Here are some of them: <a
                                    href="http://anytimecar.ru/">Anytime</a>, <a
                                    href="http://delimobil.ru/">Delimobil</a>,
                            <a href="http://car5.ru">Сar5</a>, <a href="http://belkacar.ru">BelkaCar</a> and <a
                                    href="http://youdrive.today">YouDrive</a>.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            There are three car sharing providers in Saint&nbsp;Petersburg - YouDrive, Delimobil and <a
                                    href="http://colesa.com">Colesa</a> – and two in Sochi: <a
                                    href="http://carsharing.urentcar.ru/rates.html">Urentcar</a>&nbsp;and <a
                                    href="http://sharemobil.ru/">Sherimobil</a>.
                        </p>
                    {% endblock %}
                {% endembed %}
            </ul> <!-- cd-faq-group -->
